Package com.example.event_app.models

Class Event

java.lang.Object
com.example.event_app.models.Event
public class Event extends Object
Represents an event within the LuckySpot system. This model stores all event-related information used by entrants, organizers, and administrators, including registration lists, lottery selections, geolocation data, capacity tracking, and replacement-draw history.

The event life cycle includes: waiting list registration, lottery selection, invitation response (accept/decline), replacement draws, capacity verification, and archival once the event date has passed. The model also supports tracking of geolocation audits and various participant groups.

    • Event

      public Event(String eventId, String name, String description, String organizerId)
      Creates a new event with the basic identifying information. Additional fields such as capacity, category, registration window, and poster URL may be set later.
      Parameters:
      eventId - optional event identifier stored in the document
      name - name of the event shown to users
      description - brief text describing the event
      organizerId - Firestore ID of the organizer who created the event

    • getCancellationRate

      public double getCancellationRate()
      Computes the cancellation rate as a percentage of users who were selected but later declined or cancelled. If no users were selected, this returns 0.0.
      Returns:
      cancellation rate between 0.0 and 100.0

    • hasHighCancellationRate

      public boolean hasHighCancellationRate()
      Determines whether the cancellation rate exceeds the threshold considered "high" for analytics or administrative review.
      Returns:
      true if the cancellation rate is greater than 30%, otherwise false

    • getSpotsRemaining

      public int getSpotsRemaining()
      Calculates the number of remaining available spots based on capacity and the number of users who have accepted their invitation. If no capacity is defined, the event is treated as having unlimited space.
      Returns:
      number of remaining spots, or Integer.MAX_VALUE if unlimited

    • isCapacityFull

      public boolean isCapacityFull()
      Checks whether the current number of attending users has reached or exceeded the event's capacity.
      Returns:
      true if the event is full, otherwise false

    • hasReplacementPool

      public boolean hasReplacementPool()
      Determines whether the event has a non-empty replacement pool consisting of users who did not win the initial lottery.
      Returns:
      true if the replacement pool contains at least one user

    • isPast

      public boolean isPast()
      Checks whether the event date (or server timestamp if event date is null) occurs before the current time, indicating that the event is in the past.
      Returns:
      true if the event date has passed, otherwise false
